#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:682
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration and Installation Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:684
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter introduces important parts of a control file for standard purposes. To learn about other available options, use the configuration management system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:689
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note that for some configuration options to work, additional packages need to be installed, depending on the software selection you have configured. If you choose to install a minimal system then some packages might be missing and need to be added to the individual package selection."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:696
#, no-c-format
msgid "&yast; will install packages required in the second phase of the installation and before the post-installation phase of &ay; has started. However, if necessary &yast; modules are not available in the system, important configuration steps will be skipped. For example, no security settings will be configured if <systemitem class=\"resource\">yast2-security</systemitem> is not installed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:708
#, no-c-format
msgid "General options include all the settings related to the installation process and the environment of the installed system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:713
#, no-c-format
msgid "The mode section configures the behavior of &ay; with regard to confirmation and rebooting. The following needs to be in the &lt;general&gt;&lt;mode&gt; section."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:719
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, the user must confirm the auto-installation process. This option allows the user to view and change the settings for a target system before they are committed and can be used for debugging. <literal>confirm</literal> is set to <literal>true</literal> by default to avoid recursive installs when the system schedules a reboot after initial system setup. Only disable confirmation if you want to carry out a fully unattended installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:729
#, no-c-format
msgid "With <literal>halt</literal> you cause &ay; to shut down the machine after all packages have been installed. Instead of a reboot into stage two, the machine is turned off. The boot loader is already installed and all your chroot scripts have run."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:736
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_halt</literal> and <literal>final_reboot</literal> halts or reboots the machine after the installation and the configuration are finished at the end of stage 2."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:742
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_restart_services</literal> : After installation and configuration are finished at the end of stage 2 all services will be restarted by default. With this flag set to <literal>false</literal> no restart will be done."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:749
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>activate_systemd_default_target</literal> : After installation and configuration are finished at the end of stage 2 the default target system will be activated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:755
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>ntp_sync_time_before_installation</literal> specifies the NTP server with which the system time needs to be synchronized before starting the installation on the target system. It will not be synchronized if this flag has not been used. Keep in mind that you need a reachable NTP server and network connections while running the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:763
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>max_systemd_wait</literal> specifies how long &ay; waits at most for systemd to set up the default target. Normally you do not need to bother with this entry. If it is not preset, a reasonable default (30 seconds) is used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:770
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some &opensuse; versions use the kexec feature and do not reboot anymore between stage 1 and stage 2. With the <literal>forceboot</literal> option you can force the reboot in case you need it for some reason. The value <literal>true</literal> will reboot, <literal>false</literal> will not reboot and a missing <literal>forceboot</literal> option uses the product's default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:780
#, no-c-format
msgid "Drivers May Need a Reboot"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: ay_bigfile.xml:785
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some drivers, for example the proprietary drivers for Nvidia and ATI graphics cards, need a reboot and will not work properly when using kexec. Therefore the default on &productname; products is to always do a proper reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:814
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>confirm</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:819
#, no-c-format
msgid "If this boolean is set to <literal>true</literal> , the installation stops at the confirmation screen (also called proposal screen) and needs to be confirmed with the <guimenu>Install</guimenu> button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:824
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;confirm config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  true\n"
      "&lt;/confirm&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:836
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>halt</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:841
#, no-c-format
msgid "Shuts down the machine after the first stage. So if you turn it on again, the machine boots and the second stage of the autoinstallation starts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:846
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;halt config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  true\n"
      "&lt;/halt&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:858
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>second_stage</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:863
#, no-c-format
msgid "This boolean determines if &ay; will run in the second stage too (after the partitioning, software and boot loader installation of the first stage). If you set this to <literal>false</literal> , a normal manual installation happens in the second stage."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:869
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;second_stage config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  true\n"
      "&lt;/second_stage&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:881
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_reboot</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:886
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you set this to <literal>true</literal> , the machine will reboot at the very end of the installation (when everything is installed and configured at the end of the second stage)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:891
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;final_reboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  true\n"
      "&lt;/final_reboot&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:896
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. The default is <literal>false</literal> . It makes no sense to set this and <literal>final_halt</literal> to <literal>true</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:905
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_halt</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:910
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you set this to <literal>true</literal> , the machine will shut down at the very end of the installation (when everything is installed and configured at the end of the second stage)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:915
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;final_halt config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  true\n"
      "&lt;/final_halt&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:920
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. The default is <literal>false</literal> . It makes no sense to set this and <literal>final_reboot</literal> to <literal>true</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:929
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>confirm_base_product_license</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:934
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you set this to <literal>true</literal> , the EULA of the base product will be shown. The user needs to accept this license. Otherwise the installation will be canceled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:939
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;confirm_base_product_license config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  true\n"
      "&lt;/confirm_base_product_license&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:944
#, no-c-format
msgid "Optional. The default is <literal>false</literal> . This applies to the base product license only. Use the flag <literal>confirm_license</literal> in the <literal>add-on</literal> section to show additional licenses."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:954
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>final_restart_services</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:959
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you set this entry to <literal>false</literal> , all services will <emphasis>not</emphasis> be restarted at the very end of the installation (when everything is installed and configured at the end of the second stage)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:965
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;final_restart_services config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  false\n"
      "&lt;/final_restart_services&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:977
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>activate_systemd_default_target</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:982
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you set this entry to <literal>false</literal> , the default target will not be activated via the call <command>systemctl isolate</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:987
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;activate_systemd_default_target config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  false\n"
      "&lt;/activate_systemd_default_target&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:999
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>forceboot</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1004
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some &opensuse; releases use kexec to avoid the reboot after the first stage. They immediately boot into the installed system. You can force a reboot with this:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1009
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;forceboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  true\n"
      "&lt;/forceboot&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1021
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>self_update</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1026
#, no-c-format
msgid "This option allows to enable (set to <literal>true</literal> ) or disable (set to <literal>false</literal> the self-update. Check out <xref linkend=\"sec.yast_install.self_update\"/> to find further information about this feature."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1032
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;self_update config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;\n"
      "  false\n"
      "&lt;self_update/&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1046
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>self_update_url</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1051
#, no-c-format
msgid "Location of the update repository to use during &yast; self-update. Check out the &deploy; to find further information about this feature."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1056
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installer Self-Update Repository Only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1057
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <option>self_update_url</option> parameter expects only the installer self-update repository URL. Do not supply any other repository URL&mdash;for example the URL of the software update repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1064
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;self_update_url&gt;\n"
      "  http://example.com/updates/$arch\n"
      "&lt;/self_update_url&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1067
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternatively, you can specify the boot parameter <literal>self_update</literal> on the kernel command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1072
#, no-c-format
msgid "The URL can contain a variable"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: envar
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1072
#, no-c-format
msgid "$arch"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: literal
#: ay_bigfile.xml:1074
#, no-c-format
