#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3284
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reuse only specified partitions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3286
#, no-c-format
msgid "This option allows you to select specific partitions to delete. Start the selection with the last available partition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3293
#, no-c-format
msgid "Repartitioning only works if the selected partitions are neighbors and located at the end of the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3298
#, no-c-format
msgid "Beware of Data Loss"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3299
#, no-c-format
msgid "The value provided in the <literal>use</literal> property determines how existing data and partitions are treated. The value <literal>all</literal> means that the entire disk will be erased. Make backups and use the <literal>confirm</literal> property if you need to keep some partitions with important data. Otherwise, no pop-ups will notify you about partitions being deleted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3308
#, no-c-format
msgid "If multiple drives are in the target system, identify all drives with their device names and specify how the partitioning should be performed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3313
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition sizes can be given in gigabytes, megabytes or can be set to a flexible value using the keywords <literal>auto</literal> and <literal>max</literal> . <literal>max</literal> uses all available space on a drive, therefore should only be set for the last partition on the drive. With <literal>auto</literal> the size of a <literal>swap</literal> or <literal>boot</literal> partition is determined automatically, depending on the memory available and the type of the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3323
#, no-c-format
msgid "A fixed size can be given as shown below:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:3326
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>1GB</literal> , <literal>1G</literal> , <literal>1000MB</literal> , or <literal>1000M</literal> will all create a partition of the size 1 Gigabyte."
msgstr ""

