#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15105
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Auto-Installation Process"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15111
#, no-c-format
msgid "After the system has booted into an automatic installation and the control file has been retrieved, &yast; configures the system according to the information provided in the control file. All configuration settings are summarized in a window that is shown by default and should be deactivated if a fully automatic installation is needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15120
#, no-c-format
msgid "By the time &yast; displays the summary of the configuration, &yast; has only probed hardware and prepared the system for auto-installation. Nothing has been changed in the system yet. In case of any error, you can still abort the process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15127
#, no-c-format
msgid "A system should be automatically installable without the need to have any graphic adapter or monitor. Having a monitor attached to the client machine is nevertheless recommended so you can supervise the process and to get feedback in case of errors. Choose between the graphical and the text-based Ncurses interfaces. For headless clients, system messages can be monitored using the serial console."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15137
#, no-c-format
msgid "X11 Interface (graphical)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15138
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is the default interface while auto-installing. No special variables are required to activate it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15145
#, no-c-format
msgid "Serial console"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15146
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start installing a system using the serial console by adding the keyword <literal>console</literal> (for example <literal>console=ttyS0</literal> ) to the command line of the kernel. This starts linuxrc in console mode and later &yast; in serial console mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15156
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text-based &yast; Installation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15157
#, no-c-format
msgid "This option can also be activated on the command line. To start &yast; in text mode, add <literal>textmode=1</literal> on the command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting &yast; in the text mode is recommended when installing a client with less than 64 MB or when X11 should not be configured, especially on headless machines."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15170
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choosing the Right Boot Medium"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15172
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are different methods for booting the client. The computer can boot from its network interface card (NIC) to receive the boot images via DHCP or TFTP. Alternatively a suitable kernel and initrd image can be loaded from a flash disk or a bootable DVD-ROM."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15179
#, no-c-format
msgid "&yast; will check for <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> in the root directory of the boot medium or the initrd upon start-up and switch to an automated installation if it was found. In case the control file is named differently or located elsewhere, specify its location on the kernel command line with the parameter <literal>&ay;=<replaceable>URL</replaceable></literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15189
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting from a Flash Disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15190
#, no-c-format
msgid "For testing/rescue purposes or because the NIC does not have a PROM or PXE you can build a bootable flash disk to use with &ay;. Flash disks can also store the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15196
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Bootable Flash Disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15197
#, no-c-format
msgid "To create a bootable flash disk, copy either the &productname; iso image of DVD1 or the Mini CD ISO image to the disk using the <command>dd</command> command (the flash disk must not be mounted, all data on the device will be erased):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15203
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;dd if=PATH_TO_ISO_IMAGE of=USB_STORAGE_DEVICE bs=4M"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting from DVD-ROM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15209
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use the original &productname; DVD-ROM number one in combination with other media. For example, the control file can be provided via a flash disk or a specified location on the network. Alternatively, create a customized DVD-ROM that includes the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15219
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting via PXE over the Network"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting via PXE requires a DHCP and a TFTP server in your network. The computer will then boot without a physical medium. <phrase os=\"sles;sled\">For instructions on setting up the required infrastructure, see <xref linkend=\"cha.remote_installation\"/>.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15226
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you do installation via PXE, the installation will run into an endless loop. This happens because after the first reboot, the machine performs the PXE boot again and restarts the installation instead of booting from the hard disk for the second stage of the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15233
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are several ways to solve this problem. You can use an HTTP server to provide the &ay; control file. Alternatively, instead of a static control file, run a CGI script on the Web server that provides the control file and changes the TFTP server configuration for your target host. This way, the next PXE boot of the machine will be from the hard disk by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15241
#, no-c-format
msgid "Another way is to use &ay; to upload a new PXE boot configuration for the target host via the control file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15245
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;pxe&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;pxe_localboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/pxe_localboot&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;pxelinux-config&gt;\n"
      "    DEFAULT linux\n"
      "    LABEL linux\n"
      "    localboot 0\n"
      "  &lt;/pxelinux-config&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;tftp-server&gt;&tftpip;&lt;/tftp-server&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;pxelinux-dir&gt;/pxelinux.cfg&lt;/pxelinux-dir&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;filename&gt;__MAC__&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
      "&lt;/pxe&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15256
#, no-c-format
msgid "This entry will upload a new configuration for the target host to the TFTP server shortly before the first reboot happens. In most installations the TFTP daemon runs as user <systemitem class=\"username\">nobody</systemitem> . You need to make sure this user has write permissions to the <filename>pxelinux.cfg</filename> directory. You can also configure the file name that will be uploaded. If you use the <quote>magic</quote> <literal>__MAC__</literal> file name, the file name will be the MAC address of your machine like, for example <literal>01-08-00-27-79-49-ee</literal> . If the file name setting is missing, the IP address will be used for the file name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15269
#, no-c-format
msgid "To do another auto-installation on the same machine, you need to remove the file from the TFTP server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Invoking the Auto-Installation Process"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15283
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15284
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding the command line variable <literal>autoyast</literal> causes linuxrc to start in automated mode. linuxrc searches for a configuration file, which should be distinguished from the main control file in the following places:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15292
#, no-c-format
msgid "in the root directory of the initial RAM disk used for booting the system,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15298
#, no-c-format
msgid "in the root directory of the boot medium"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15303
#, no-c-format
msgid "The configuration file used by linuxrc can have the following keywords (for a detailed description of how linuxrc works and other keywords, see <xref linkend=\"appendix.linuxrc\"/> ):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15309
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keywords for linuxrc"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15314
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keyword"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15319
#, no-c-format
msgid "Value"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15328
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoupgrade</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15333
#, no-c-format
msgid "Initiate an automatic upgrade using &ay;. Also requires the <literal>autoyast</literal> parameter (see <xref linkend=\"Commandline.ay\"/> for details)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15342
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15347
#, no-c-format
msgid "Location of the control file for automatic installation, see <xref linkend=\"Commandline.ay\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15355
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast2</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Location of the control file for automatic installation. Similar to <literal>autoyast</literal> option but linuxrc parses the provided value and, for example, tries to configure a network when needed. For information about differences between the &ay; and linuxrc URI syntax, see the documentation of linuxrc. &ay;'s rules and classes are not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15372
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>ifcfg</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15377
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure and start the network. Required if the &ay; is to be fetched from a remote location. See <xref linkend=\"ay.adv_network\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15413
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>insmod</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15418
#, no-c-format
msgid "Kernel modules to load"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15425
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>install</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Location of the installation directory, for example <literal>install=nfs://192.168.2.1/CDs/</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15438
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>instmode</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15443
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation mode, for example <literal>nfs</literal> , <literal>http</literal> etc. (not needed if <literal>install</literal> is set)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15491
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>rootpassword</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15496
#, no-c-format
msgid "Password for root user if not specified in &ay; profile"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15503
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>server</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15508
#, no-c-format
msgid "Server (NFS) to contact for source directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15515
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>serverdir</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15520
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directory on NFS Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15532
#, no-c-format
msgid "Even with &lt;confirm&gt;no&lt;/confirm&gt; in the control file, the confirm proposal comes up."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15541
#, no-c-format
msgid "These variables and keywords will bring the system up to the point where &yast; can take over with the main control file. Currently, the source medium is automatically discovered, which in some cases makes it possible to initiate the auto-install process without giving any instructions to linuxrc."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15548
#, no-c-format
msgid "The traditional linuxrc configuration file ( <filename>info</filename> ) has the function of giving the client enough information about the installation server and the location of the sources. Usually, this file is not required; but it is needed in special network environments where DHCP and BOOTP are not used or when special kernel modules need to be loaded."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: #text
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15561
#, no-c-format
msgid "All linuxrc keywords can be passed to linuxrc using the kernel command line. The command line can also be set when creating network bootable images or it can be passed to the kernel using a specially configured DHCP server in combination with Etherboot or PXE."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15565
#, no-c-format
msgid "The command line variable <literal>autoyast</literal> can be used in the format described in table <quote><xref linkend=\"Commandline.ay\"/></quote>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15571
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Variables for &ay;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15576
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command line variable"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15590
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=default</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15595
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default auto-installation option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15602
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=file:///<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15607
#, no-c-format
msgid "Looks for control file in specified path (relative to the source root directory, for example <literal>file:///autoinst.xml</literal> if in the top directory of a CD-ROM and you did an installation from CD)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=device://<replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>/<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15622
#, no-c-format
msgid "Looks for control file on a storage device. Do not specify the full path to the device, but the device name only. You may also omit specifying the device and trigger &ay; to search all devices ( <literal>autoyast=device:///<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></literal> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15632
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=nfs://<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15637
#, no-c-format
msgid "Looks for control file on an NFS server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15644
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=http://[user:password@]<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15649
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieves the control file from a Web server using the HTTP protocol. Specifying a user name and a password is optional."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15657
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=https://[user:password@]<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15662
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieves the control file from a Web server using HTTPS. Specifying a user name and a password is optional."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15670
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=tftp://<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15675
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieve the control file via TFTP."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15682
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=ftp://[user:password@]<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15687
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieve the control file via FTP. Specifying a user name and a password is optional."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15695
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=usb://<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15700
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieve the control file from USB devices (&ay; will search all connected USB devices)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15708
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=relurl://<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15713
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieve the control file from the installation source (install=....)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15721
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=slp</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15726
#, no-c-format
msgid "Query the location of the control file from an SLP server (service:autoyast:...). Optionally you may add a <literal>description=</literal> attribute so you can <quote>translate</quote> the URL into something more readable. ( <literal>autoyast=slp:/?descr=*SLES*</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15737
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=cifs://<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15742
#, no-c-format
msgid "Looks for control file on a CIFS server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15749
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=label://<replaceable>LABEL</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15754
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searches for a control file on a device with the specified label"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15762
#, no-c-format
msgid "Several scenarios for auto-installation are possible using different types of infrastructure and source media. The simplest way is to use the source media (DVD number one) of &productname;. But to initiate the auto-installation process, the auto-installation command-line variable should be entered at system boot-up and the control file should be accessible for &yast;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15770
#, no-c-format
msgid "In a scripting context, you can use a serial console for your virtual machine, that allows you to work in text mode. Then you can pass the needed parameters from an expect script or equivalent."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15773
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following list of scenarios explains how the control file can be supplied:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15778
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Original &productname; DVD-ROM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15780
#, no-c-format
msgid "When using the original DVD-ROM (DVD #1 is needed), the control file needs to be accessible via flash disk or network:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15807
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using a Custom DVD-ROM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15809
#, no-c-format
msgid "In this case, you can include the control file directly on the DVD-ROM. When placing it in the root directory and naming it <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> , it will automatically be found and used for the installation. Otherwise use <literal>autoyast=file:///<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal> to specify the path to the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15817
#, no-c-format
msgid "When using a DVD-ROM for auto-installation, it is necessary to instruct the installer to use the DVD-ROM for installation instead of trying to find the installation files on the network. This can be done by adding the <literal>instmode=cd</literal> option to the kernel command line (this can be automated by adding the option to the <filename>isolinux.cfg</filename> file on the DVD)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15828
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using a Network Installation Source"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15830
#, no-c-format
msgid "This option is the most important one because installations of multiple machines are usually done using SLP or NFS servers and other network services like BOOTP and DHCP. The easiest way to make the control file available is to place it in the root directory of the installation source naming it <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> . In this case it will automatically be found and used for the installation. The control file can also reside in the following places:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15841
#, no-c-format
msgid "Flash Disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15842
#, no-c-format
msgid "Access the control file via the <literal>autoyast=usb://<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15849
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15850
#, no-c-format
msgid "Access the control file via the following commands: <literal>autoyast=nfs://..</literal> , <literal>autoyast=ftp://..</literal> , <literal>autoyast=http://..</literal> , <literal>autoyast=https://..</literal> , <literal>autoyast=tftp://..</literal> , or <literal>autoyast=cifs://..</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15864
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling Network and DHCP"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15865
#, no-c-format
msgid "To disable the network during installations where it is not needed or unavailable, for example when auto-installing from DVD-ROMs, use the linuxrc option <literal>netsetup=0</literal> to disable the network setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15873
#, no-c-format
msgid "Difference between the <literal>autoyast</literal> and <literal>autoyast2</literal> Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15877
#, no-c-format
msgid "The options <literal>autoyast</literal> and <literal>autoyast2</literal> are very similar but differ in one important point:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15883
#, no-c-format
msgid "When you use <literal>autoyast=http://...</literal> , you need to provide linuxrc with the network configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15889
#, no-c-format
msgid "When you use <literal>autoyast2=http://...</literal> , linuxrc tries to configure the network for you."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15896
#, no-c-format
msgid "If <literal>autoyast=default</literal> is defined, &yast; will look for a file named <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> in the following three places:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15903
#, no-c-format
msgid "the root directory of the flash disk,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15908
#, no-c-format
msgid "the root directory of the installation medium,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15913
#, no-c-format
msgid "the root directory of the initial RAM disk used to boot the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15918
#, no-c-format
msgid "With all &ay; invocation options, excluding <literal>default</literal> , it is possible to specify the location of the control file in the following ways:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15926
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify the exact location of the control file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15929
#, no-c-format
msgid "autoyast=http://192.168.1.1/control-files/client01.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15932
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify a directory where several control files are located:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15935
#, no-c-format
msgid "autoyast=http://192.168.1.1/control-files/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15936
#, no-c-format
msgid "In this case the relevant control file is retrieved using the hex digit representation of the IP as described below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15942
#, no-c-format
msgid "If only the path prefix variable is defined, &yast; will fetch the control file from the specified location in the following way:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15949
#, no-c-format
msgid "First, it will search for the control file using its own IP address in uppercase hexadecimal, for example <literal>192.0.2.91 -&gt; C000025B</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15956
#, no-c-format
msgid "If this file is not found, &yast; will remove one hex digit and try again. This action is repeated until the file with the correct name is found. Ultimately, it will try looking for a file with the MAC address of the client as the file name (mac should have the following syntax: <literal>0080C8F6484C</literal> ) and if not found a file named <filename>default</filename> (in lowercase)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15966
#, no-c-format
msgid "As an example, for 192.0.2.91, the HTTP client will try:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15970
#, no-c-format
msgid "C000025B\n"
      "C000025\n"
      "C00002\n"
      "C0000\n"
      "C000\n"
      "C00\n"
      "C0\n"
      "C\n"
      "0080C8F6484C\n"
      "default"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15980
#, no-c-format
msgid "in that order."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15983
#, no-c-format
msgid "To determine the hex representation of the IP address of the client, use the utility called <command>/usr/bin/gethostip</command> available with the <systemitem class=\"resource\">syslinux</systemitem> package."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15989
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determine HEX code for an IP address"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15990
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;/usr/bin/gethostip 10.10.0.1\n"
